# Refinement Rule

Load this rule when you need the repair contract for regenerating an existing slide after critique.

## Required inputs

- `Current JSON`
- `Feedback`
- `Slide Plan`
- `Design Skills and Requirements`

## Repair behavior

- Fix the current slide based on the feedback instead of inventing a new concept.
- Preserve the intended narrative unless the feedback proves the original structure is unusable.
- Reapply the Leafer Javascript construction contracts from `references/authoring/code/canvas-and-elements`, `references/authoring/code/layout-and-transform`, and `references/authoring/code/visual-style`; also load `references/authoring/code/animation-and-motion` when the repaired slide contains motion.
- Load `references/authoring/visual/common-errors` before finalizing the repaired result.

## Output contract

- Regenerate the updated `SlideData` structure only.
- The `code` field must contain the repaired Leafer Javascript implementation.
- If the caller asks for structured output, return only the updated structured payload and no extra commentary outside that payload.
